            <p>127 West 13<hi rend="sup">th</hi> St. Aug. 16. 5618.<lb/>
                Revd. S. Morais&#44;<lb/>
                Reverend and dear Sir&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>It is<lb/> with sincere pleasure that I am enabled to<lb/> inform you that Dr. Bachman the Gentleman<lb/> for whom you have interested yourself&#45;and me&#45;<lb/> has been accepted&#44; under the annexed con&#45;<lb/>ditions.  1st That he enter the Hospital as<lb/> a Patient&#44; that is to say&#45;no services will be<lb/> expected of him&#59; and 2ndly that if after the<lb/> lapse of 2 or 3 months no improvement is dis&#45;<lb/>cernible or in prospect that he be taken care of<lb/> by some of his Friends in Philada.<lb/></p>
            <p>This latter condition is rendered necessary by the<lb/> facts that the rules of the Hospital forbid<lb/> the detention of incurable cases&#45;and&#45;by<lb/> the low state of the funds.<lb/></p>
            <p>Please inform Dr. B. that with<lb/> this understanding he may present him&#45;<lb/>self at his earliest convenience.<lb/></p>
            <p>Hoping dear Sir&#44; that<lb/></p>
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>you are satisfied with my efforts<lb/> and with sincere regards for your<lb/>self and your lovely Family.<lb/>
                I remain<lb/>
                Truly Yours<lb/>
                Mark Blumenthal M. D.<lb/></p>
                
            <p>N.B. Orders have been given for the admission<lb/> of Dr. B. on presenting enclosed<lb/> permit.<lb/></p>
            
        </body>
    </text>
